From <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Despatch_rider" rel="nofollow">Wikipedia</a>:</i>

&quot;A despatch rider is a military messenger, mounted on horse or motorcycle.

&quot;Despatch riders were used by armed forces to deliver urgent orders and messages between headquarters and military units. They had a vital role at a time when telecommunications were limited and insecure. In the British Army, motorcycle despatch riders were first used in the World War I by the Royal Engineers Signal Service. The riders were originally volunteers, some of whom supplied their own machines.&quot;
